---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CtaBand from "../components/CtaBand.astro";
import EvidenceWorkspace from "../components/EvidenceWorkspace.astro";
import { site } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout title="ControlPlane: The Regulated Application Delivery System" description={`The platform direction for ${site.name}: reusable application foundations, structured validation evidence, controlled releases, and deployment adapters for life-sciences teams.`}>
  <section class="platform-hero">
    <div class="wrap hero-grid">
      <div data-reveal>
        <div class="hero-meta"><span>07 / 07</span><span>Platform direction</span></div>
        <span class="eyebrow mint">ControlPlane</span>
        <h1>Reuse the system behind every application.</h1>
        <p>Every application improves a shared set of templates, controls, tests, validation records, and release automation. Once those parts are proven across a portfolio, customer and partner developers can use them too.</p>
        <a class="button button-mint" href="/contact">Discuss the platform path <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
      <div class="evidence-graph" data-reveal aria-label="Traceability chain connecting a requirement to an approved release">
        <span class="graph-label">traceability chain / release 1.8.2</span>
        <div class="evidence-chain">
          <div class="graph-node"><small>REQ</small><strong>4.2</strong><span>Calculation review</span></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div class="graph-node"><small>RISK</small><strong>R-07</strong><span>Incorrect result</span></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div class="graph-node"><small>CTRL</small><strong>C-12</strong><span>Independent check</span></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div class="graph-node"><small>TEST</small><strong>E2E-14</strong><span>Passed</span></div>
          <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
          <div class="graph-node release"><small>RELEASE</small><strong>1.8.2</strong><span>Approved</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="graph-summary"><span>Requirement covered</span><span>Current evidence linked</span><strong>Release approved ✓</strong></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status section-pad-small">
    <div class="content-wrap status-grid" data-reveal><span>Read this first</span><div><h2>ControlPlane is the future direction, not a product for sale today.</h2><p>It begins as internal infrastructure used to deliver each application. It becomes a customer-facing platform only after the templates and controls are proven across multiple applications and external teams ask to use them.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="layers section-pad">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-heading" data-reveal><div><span class="eyebrow">What gets reused</span><h2>One application delivery layer across the platforms you already own.</h2></div><p>ControlPlane would not replace data lakes, notebooks, compute platforms, QMS, or validation repositories. It would connect application development, testing, validation evidence, and releases across those systems.</p></div>
      <div class="platform-artifact" data-reveal>
        <div class="artifact-copy"><span class="eyebrow">A linked release record</span><h3>Keep validation evidence connected instead of assembling it at the end.</h3><p>Requirements, risks, controls, test results, approvals, and releases remain linked as the application changes. Approved documents can be generated from the current record.</p><ul><li>Trace a requirement to its current test result</li><li>See which controls a change may affect</li><li>Assemble the evidence for a release package</li></ul></div>
        <EvidenceWorkspace compact />
      </div>
      <div class="layer-stack" data-reveal>
        <article class="layer-apps"><span>Scientific products</span><div><b>Submission review</b><b>Lab analytics</b><b>Model-enabled apps</b><b>Regulatory evidence</b></div></article>
        <article class="layer-control"><span>{site.name} ControlPlane</span><div><b>Templates & SDK</b><b>Regulated components</b><b>Evidence graph</b><b>Release gates</b><b>App catalog</b></div></article>
        <article class="layer-platform"><span>Customer platforms</span><div><b>Domino</b><b>Posit</b><b>Databricks</b><b>Kubernetes</b><b>AWS / Azure / GCP</b></div></article>
        <article class="layer-systems"><span>Systems of record</span><div><b>Data lakes</b><b>LIMS / ELN</b><b>Veeva</b><b>Kneat</b><b>ValGenesis</b><b>Jira / ServiceNow</b></div></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="modules section-pad">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-heading" data-reveal><div><span class="eyebrow mint">Platform modules</span><h2>The reusable foundation beneath every release.</h2></div><p>These capabilities are built first to make application delivery faster and more reliable. Requirements, tests, approvals, and release details remain linked; approved documents are generated from those records.</p></div>
      <div class="module-grid" data-reveal>
        <article><span>01</span><h3>Application SDK</h3><p>Opinionated R/Shiny, Python, and web templates with testing, security, observability, and deployment metadata preconfigured.</p></article>
        <article><span>02</span><h3>Regulated components</h3><p>Reusable identity, review, approval, reason-for-change, audit event, data lineage, reconciliation, and reporting patterns.</p></article>
        <article><span>03</span><h3>Linked validation record</h3><p>Connections from each requirement to its risks, controls, code, test results, defects, approvals, and releases.</p></article>
        <article><span>04</span><h3>Change and release control</h3><p>Change detection, impact assessment, regression-test selection, evidence assembly, deviation handling, and release approval.</p></article>
        <article><span>05</span><h3>Deployment adapters</h3><p>Customer-owned delivery across Domino, Posit Connect, Databricks, Kubernetes, and existing CI/CD systems.</p></article>
        <article><span>06</span><h3>System integrations</h3><p>Push approved records into the organization’s QMS, validation, service, and document systems instead of displacing them.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="trigger section-pad">
    <div class="wrap trigger-grid">
      <div data-reveal><span class="eyebrow">When it becomes a product</span><h2>The platform comes after repeated application delivery.</h2></div>
      <div class="trigger-list" data-reveal><p>ControlPlane becomes a standalone offer when:</p><ul><li>It supports every {site.name} project</li><li>10–15 applications have been deployed through it</li><li>It has processed dozens of controlled releases</li><li>Reusable components materially reduce development and validation effort</li><li>Customer teams ask to build through the same controls</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand eyebrow="Build toward the platform" title="Start with an application that solves a real problem." text="The shared platform should grow from applications that have handled real data, controlled changes, and approved releases. Let’s identify the first process worth improving." label="Find the first application" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .platform-hero { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); padding: clamp(5rem, 9vw, 9rem) 0; }
  .hero-grid { align-items: center; display: grid; gap: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 9rem); grid-template-columns: 0.9fr 1.1fr; }
  .hero-meta { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); color: var(--mint); display: flex; font-size: .64rem; font-weight: 800; justify-content: space-between; letter-spacing: .1em; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .platform-hero h1 { color: var(--paper); font-size: clamp(3.8rem, 7vw, 7.6rem); margin: 1rem 0 2rem; }
  .platform-hero p { color: var(--white-soft); max-width: 40rem; }
  .platform-hero .button { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: 1; background: #0b2325; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); overflow: hidden; position: relative; }
  .graph-label { color: var(--mint); font-size: .55rem; left: 1rem; letter-spacing: .1em; position: absolute; text-transform: uppercase; top: 1rem; }
  .evidence-graph svg { inset: 0; position: absolute; }
  .evidence-graph path { fill: none; stroke: rgba(212,255,116,.45); stroke-dasharray: 5 5; stroke-width: 1.2; }
  .graph-node { background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--mint); color: var(--ink); display: grid; height: 8rem; padding: .8rem; position: absolute; width: 8rem; z-index: 2; }
  .graph-node small { color: var(--teal); font-size: .5rem; font-weight: 800; }.graph-node strong { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 500; }.graph-node span { align-self: end; color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: .55rem; }
  .requirement { left: 7%; top: 10%; }.risk { right: 9%; top: 19%; }.control { left: 40%; top: 40%; }.test { bottom: 10%; right: 10%; }.release { bottom: 7%; left: 9%; background: var(--mint); }
  .status { background: var(--accent); }
  .status-grid { display: grid; gap: 2rem; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; }
  .status-grid > span { border: 1px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 999px; font-size: .65rem; font-weight: 800; height: fit-content; padding: .4rem .7rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .status h2 { font-size: clamp(2rem,4vw,4rem); margin-bottom: 1rem; }.status p { color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }
  .layers { background: var(--paper); }
  .layer-stack { border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); padding: 1rem; }
  .layer-stack article { display: grid; gap: 1rem; grid-template-columns: 12rem 1fr; padding: 1rem; }
  .layer-stack article + article { border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .layer-stack article > span { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: .65rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .08em; padding: .7rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .layer-stack article div { display: grid; gap: .6rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit,minmax(8rem,1fr)); }
  .layer-stack b { background: var(--wash); font-size: .7rem; padding: .9rem; text-align: center; }
  .layer-control { background: var(--teal); color: var(--paper); }.layer-control > span { color: var(--mint) !important; }.layer-control b { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); }
  .modules { background: var(--teal); color: var(--paper); }
  .modules :global(.section-heading h2) { color: var(--paper); }.modules :global(.section-heading p) { color: var(--white-soft); }
  .module-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr); }
  .module-grid article { border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.25); min-height: 22rem; padding: 2rem; }
  .module-grid span { color: var(--mint); font-size: .65rem; font-weight: 800; }.module-grid h3 { color: var(--paper); margin: 5rem 0 1rem; }.module-grid p { color: var(--white-soft); font-size: .82rem; }
  .trigger { background: var(--paper-deep); }
  .trigger-grid { display: grid; gap: clamp(3rem,8vw,9rem); grid-template-columns: .9fr 1.1fr; }
  .trigger h2 { margin: 1rem 0 0; max-width: 12ch; }
  .trigger-list > p { color: var(--ink); font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.4rem; }
  .trigger-list ul { list-style: none; margin: 2rem 0 0; padding: 0; }
  .trigger-list li { border-top: 1px solid var(--line-strong); color: var(--ink-soft); padding: 1rem 0 1rem 2rem; position: relative; }.trigger-list li::before { color: var(--accent-strong); content: "✓"; left: 0; position: absolute; }
  @media(max-width:900px){.hero-grid,.trigger-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.evidence-graph{max-width:40rem}.module-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
  @media(max-width:650px){.graph-node{height:6rem;width:6rem}.layer-stack article{grid-template-columns:1fr}.module-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.status-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>

<style>
  .platform-artifact { align-items: center; background: var(--paper-deep); border-radius: var(--radius); display: grid; gap: clamp(2.5rem,5vw,5rem); grid-template-columns: minmax(18rem,.65fr) minmax(0,1.35fr); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; overflow: hidden; padding: clamp(1.5rem,4vw,4rem); }
  .artifact-copy h3 { font-size: clamp(2rem,3.4vw,3.5rem); margin: 1.3rem 0; max-width: 14ch; }
  .artifact-copy p { font-size: .98rem; }
  .artifact-copy ul { list-style: none; margin: 2rem 0 0; padding: 0; }
  .artifact-copy li { border-top: 1px solid var(--line-strong); color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: .84rem; padding: .8rem 0 .8rem 1.5rem; position: relative; }
  .artifact-copy li::before { color: var(--accent-strong); content: "→"; left: 0; position: absolute; }

  @media(max-width:950px) {
    .platform-artifact { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .artifact-copy h3 { max-width: 18ch; }
  }
</style>

<style>
  .platform-hero { background: #050706; padding: clamp(5rem,9vw,8rem) 0 0; }
  .hero-grid { gap: clamp(4rem,7vw,6rem); grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .hero-grid > div:first-child { margin-inline: auto; max-width: 68rem; text-align: center; }
  .hero-meta { border: 0; display: inline-flex; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 500; gap: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding: .5rem .8rem; }
  .platform-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(3.8rem,7.2vw,7.4rem); line-height: .94; margin: 1.4rem auto 2rem; max-width: 13ch; }
  .platform-hero p { margin-inline: auto; max-width: 48rem; }
  .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: 16/8; background: #112f25; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14); border-radius: 1.25rem 1.25rem 0 0; margin-inline: auto; max-width: 72rem; width: 100%; }
  .graph-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .evidence-graph svg { height: 130%; left: 10%; top: -15%; width: 80%; }
  .graph-node { border: 0; border-radius: .75rem; box-shadow: 0 16px 45px rgba(0,0,0,.18); }
  .requirement { left: 10%; top: 13%; }.risk { right: 11%; top: 18%; }.control { left: 43%; top: 36%; }.test { bottom: 10%; right: 14%; }.release { bottom: 8%; left: 13%; }

  .status { background: var(--accent); }
  .status-grid { align-items: start; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; }
  .status-grid > span { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 500; }
  .layers { background: var(--paper); }
  .layer-stack { background: var(--paper-deep); border: 0; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1rem; }
  .layer-stack article { border-radius: .8rem; margin-bottom: .5rem; }
  .layer-stack article + article { border-top: 0; }
  .layer-stack b { border-radius: .45rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .65rem; font-weight: 500; }

  .modules { background: #133c2d; }
  .module-grid { gap: .8rem; }
  .module-grid article { background: rgba(255,255,255,.07); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12); border-radius: 1rem; min-height: 21rem; }
  .module-grid h3 { margin-top: 4.5rem; }

  .trigger { background: var(--paper-deep); }
  .trigger-list { background: var(--paper); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.5rem); }
  .trigger-list > p { font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .trigger-list li:first-child { border-top: 0; }

  @media(max-width:900px) {
    .hero-grid,
    .trigger-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: 4/3; max-width: 44rem; }
    .module-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  @media(max-width:650px) {
    .platform-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(3.1rem,14vw,4.5rem); }
    .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: 1; }
    .graph-node { height: 5.5rem; width: 5.5rem; }
    .layer-stack article { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .module-grid,
    .status-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>

<style>
  .hero-meta { font-size: .7rem; }
  .graph-label { font-size: .62rem; }
  .graph-node small { font-size: .58rem; }
  .graph-node span { font-size: .63rem; }
  .status-grid > span { font-size: .7rem; }
  .layer-stack article > span { font-size: .72rem; }
  .layer-stack b { font-size: .72rem; }
  .module-grid article { min-height: 18rem; }
  .module-grid h3 { margin-top: 3.35rem; }
  .module-grid p { font-size: .91rem; }
  .module-grid span { font-size: .72rem; }
  .trigger-list li { font-size: .94rem; }

  @media(max-width:650px) {
    .module-grid article { min-height: 16rem; }
  }
</style>

<style>
  /* Traceability is shown as a readable chain, not a decorative orbit. */
  .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: auto; background: #112f25; display: block; margin-inline: auto; max-width: 62rem; min-height: 18rem; overflow: visible; padding: 1.3rem; position: relative; width: 100%; }
  .graph-label { display: block; left: auto; position: static; top: auto; }
  .evidence-chain { align-items: stretch; display: grid; gap: .45rem; grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) auto minmax(0,1fr) auto minmax(0,1fr) auto minmax(0,1fr) auto minmax(0,1fr); margin-top: 2.1rem; }
  .evidence-chain > i { align-self: center; color: var(--mint); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .72rem; font-style: normal; }
  .graph-node { background: #f7f8f3; border: 0; border-radius: .7rem; box-shadow: none; color: var(--ink); display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: auto; min-height: 7.4rem; padding: .8rem; position: static; width: auto; }
  .graph-node small { color: var(--teal); font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .graph-node strong { font-size: 1.15rem; margin-top: .5rem; }
  .graph-node span { margin-top: auto; padding-top: .7rem; }
  .graph-node.release { background: var(--mint); bottom: auto; left: auto; }
  .graph-summary { align-items: center; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.15); color: #c8d2cc; display: flex; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .58rem; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: flex-end; margin-top: 1.2rem; padding-top: .9rem; }
  .graph-summary strong { color: var(--mint); font-weight: 550; }

  @media(max-width:900px) {
    .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: auto; max-width: 48rem; min-height: 17rem; }
  }
  @media(max-width:650px) {
    .evidence-graph { aspect-ratio: auto; max-width: 31rem; min-height: 0; padding: 1rem; }
    .evidence-chain { grid-template-columns: 1fr; margin-top: 1.3rem; }
    .evidence-chain > i { font-size: .55rem; justify-self: center; line-height: .55; transform: rotate(90deg); }
    .graph-node { align-items: center; display: grid; gap: 0 .75rem; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; height: auto; min-height: 3.7rem; padding: .55rem .7rem; width: auto; }
    .graph-node small { grid-column: 1; }
    .graph-node strong { grid-column: 1; margin-top: .1rem; }
    .graph-node span { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1 / 3; justify-self: end; padding-top: 0; text-align: right; }
    .graph-summary { align-items: center; flex-direction: row; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .4rem 1rem; justify-content: flex-start; }
  }
</style>
